main event: The report describes multiple radar sightings of an unidentified object over Japan in 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed on radar, indicating it was a real physical phenomenon.
The object remained stationary and made no maneuvers during the observation period.
The object was estimated to be approximately 1/4 the size of a previously observed object.
The object was observed for around 23 minutes, from 1207 to 1230.
The object's speed was estimated to be approximately 200 knots.
sighted object: A single bright, white, elliptical-shaped object with blinking lights
